## Delivered Changes

### 1) Domain/DB Split Scaffolding
Added new module boundaries while preserving compatibility with current code:
- domain facade: domain/snipe_types.py
- db facades: db/models.py, db/migrations.py

These provide stable import paths for future Phase 2/3 moves away from the monolithic models.py.

### 2) Service Layer Added
Created service modules:
- services/battery_service.py
- services/tba_service.py
- services/sync_service.py
- services/__init__.py (lazy service accessors)

Key business logic now lives in services instead of route handlers:
- battery fetch + battery update workflow
- checkout/check-in transition handling in battery updates
- TBA single/multi assignment workflow

### 3) High-Impact API Migration
Refactored API handlers to call services:
- /api/battery/<battery_id> (GET/PUT) now uses BatteryService
- /api/tba/assign_battery now uses TbaService

This reduced route complexity and concentrated mutation logic in reusable modules.

### 4) Bootstrap/Schema Wiring Update
Updated bootstrap_db.py to use new DB facade modules:
- imports now come from db/models.py and db/migrations.py

### 5) Model Hygiene Fixes
Applied Phase 2 data-layer cleanup in models.py:
- removed duplicate Company domain struct declaration
- fixed LocationDb.__repr__ to reference real fields

